<plot>Set on the night of the biggest lottery drawing in history, Lucky Days follows the stories of seven lucky ticket holders as we discover who wins, who loses - and who really comes out ahead of the game. Taking place in real time, the film inter-cuts between the parallel story lines as the characters pass through the inevitable stages of disinterest, excitement, hope and desperation. As they come within a hair's breadth of having all their material dreams come true, they're forced to decide what really matters in their lives, and whether they have the power to turn tragedy into comedy.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?346604</url></doc>
